---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const title = 'Responsible Drinking & Our Editorial Stance | Mind the Pour';
const description = 'Mind the Pour publishes educational content about the alcohol industry for adults 21+. We do not promote drinking. Guidance on drinking responsibly and where to get help.';
---
<Base title={title} description={description}>
  <h1>Drink smart. Mind the pour.</h1>
  <p>Mind the Pour is educational content about the <em>economics and culture</em> of alcohol in India,
  intended for adults of legal drinking age (<strong>21+</strong>, or as applicable in your state).
  We do not encourage anyone to start drinking or to drink more.</p>

  <h2>The basics</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>A "standard drink" is roughly a 30ml peg of spirits — a "large" is about two.</li>
    <li>Never drink and drive. Arrange a cab or a designated driver.</li>
    <li>Pace with water and food; know your limit and respect it.</li>
    <li>Never pressure anyone to drink. Look out for friends.</li>
    <li>If drinking feels hard to control, that's worth talking to a professional about.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>If you or someone you know needs help</h2>
  <p>Speak to a doctor or a qualified counsellor. National mental-health and de-addiction helplines
  exist in India (e.g. the government's Tele-MANAS mental-health helpline). If someone is in immediate
  danger, contact local emergency services.</p>

  <p style="color:var(--stone);font-size:.85rem">This page is general information, not medical advice.</p>
</Base>
